  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and cut the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into chips</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>sweet potato chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp  </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Slice 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> discs from the <strong>cucumber </strong>(these will go in your sandwich later!)</p>\n<p>Slice the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice the halves into wedges</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-2.n-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-2.n-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-2.n-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-2.n-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-2.n-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped dill</strong>, <strong>black</strong> <strong>mustard seeds</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a splash of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl and stir until dissolved</p>\n<p>Add <strong>all</strong> of the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to the vinegar, give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1296.-step-3.n-x200.jpg",
